<title>USA: Adobe, Hillenbrand added to S&amp;P.</title>
<headline>Adobe, Hillenbrand added to S&amp;P.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Standard &amp; Poor's said Wednesday it will replace Santa Fe Pacific Gold Corp in the S&amp;P 500 Index with Adobe Systems Inc, now a component of the S&amp;P MidCap 400 Index, after Monday, May 5.</p>
<p>Santa Fe Pacific Gold Corp is being acquired by Newmont Mining Corp in a stock merger.</p>
<p>S&amp;P said Hillenbrand Industries Inc will take Santa Fe Pacific Gold's place in the S&amp;P MidCap 400 Index.</p>
<p>Adobe Systems, headquartered in San Jose, California, develops and markets computer software used to create, display, print, and communicate electronic documents.</p>
<p>Hillenbrand Industries makes hospital equipment, burial caskets, and high-security locks. The company is headquartered in Batesville, Indiana.</p>
